					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think it'd be a lot easier to start with NROM with expansion RAM (and solve all the &quot;how do you emulate CHIP8 at all&quot;),<br /> followed by porting to something with CHR-RAM (and then solve the &quot;how to emulate CHIP-8 with limited bandwidth to the emulated CPU's RAM)<br /> and only then port to this &quot;no cart memory&quot; model (and solve the &quot;how to deal with fragmented memory)<br /><br />This process of breaking it into manageable chunks is basically what one learns in first-level classes in project management.</div>

